# Privacy Policy

**Last Updated:** June 16, 2026

This Privacy Policy explains how **Document Scanner - PDF Creator and Editor** (“we”, “our”, or “the app”) handles information when you use the app.

## 1. Overview

Document Scanner - PDF Creator and Editor is a PDF and document utility app that helps you scan, view, create, convert, compress, split, merge, annotate, secure, and manage documents on your device.

Most document processing happens locally on your device. We do not run our own server for uploading or storing your documents.

## 2. Information We Do Not Collect Directly

We do not require user registration.

We do not directly collect or store personal information such as:

- Name
- Email address
- Phone number
- Contacts
- Precise location
- Payment card details
- Account passwords

We do not create a user account system inside the app.

## 3. Files and Documents

The app may access files and documents that you choose to open or that are available on your device, including:

- PDF files
- Images
- Word documents
- Excel spreadsheets
- PowerPoint presentations

This access is used only to provide app features such as:

- Opening and viewing files
- Scanning documents to PDF
- Creating and editing PDFs
- Converting files between formats
- Compressing, splitting, merging, rotating, and organizing PDFs
- Adding signatures, watermarks, annotations, or metadata
- Showing recent and previously opened files inside the app

Files are processed locally whenever possible. We do not upload your documents to our own servers.

## 4. Storage Access

Depending on your Android version and the app build you use, the app may request storage access or broad file access so it can browse and open documents on your device.

This permission is used only for document-related features. It is not used for advertising profiling, analytics, or background collection of your personal files.

You can revoke storage permissions at any time in your device settings.

## 5. Camera Access

The app may request camera permission for scanning documents to PDF.

Camera access is used only when you choose to scan a document. Captured images are processed locally on your device and used to create PDF files.

We do not upload camera images to our own servers.

You can revoke camera permission at any time in your device settings.

## 6. Local Data Stored on Your Device

The app may store limited data locally on your device, including:

- Recent file references
- App settings and preferences
- Cache files
- Output files created by you
- Premium entitlement state
- Review prompt preferences

This data stays on your device unless you choose to delete it, export it, or share it.

You can clear app data from Android settings or uninstall the app to remove local data.

## 7. Advertising

The Play Store version of the app may show ads through Google AdMob.

AdMob and Google may collect and process certain information to provide, limit, personalize, and measure ads. This may include:

- Advertising ID
- Device information
- IP address
- App interaction data
- Ad performance data
- Diagnostic information
- Approximate location inferred from IP address

We do not directly control Google’s data processing through AdMob.

The F-Droid and open-source builds do not include Google Ads SDK.

You can manage ad personalization settings from your Google account or device settings, including resetting or deleting your Advertising ID where available.

## 8. In-App Purchases and Premium

The Play Store version of the app may offer in-app purchases to unlock premium, ad-free features.

Purchases are processed through Google Play Billing. We do not receive or store your payment card details.

If you purchase premium access, the app stores a local entitlement state on your device so the app can remove ads and unlock premium features.

The F-Droid and open-source builds do not include Google Play Billing.

## 9. Third-Party Services

Depending on the app build and feature set, the app may use the following third-party services:

- Google AdMob for ads
- Google Play Billing for in-app purchases
- Google Play In-App Review for app rating prompts
- Google ML Kit or open-source OCR libraries for text recognition
- Open-source PDF and document processing libraries

These services may process data according to their own privacy policies.

## 10. Data Sharing

We do not sell your personal data.

We do not share your documents with third parties for our own business purposes.

However, third-party services such as Google AdMob and Google Play Billing may process relevant data as part of their services, according to their own policies.

## 11. Data Retention

We keep local app data only as long as needed for app functionality.

You can remove local data by:

- Clearing recent history in the app
- Clearing app cache or app data in Android settings
- Deleting generated output files manually
- Uninstalling the app

We do not maintain a server-side user database.

## 12. Children’s Privacy

The app is not specifically directed to children under 13.

We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If a parent or guardian believes a child has provided personal information, they should contact us so we can review the issue.

## 13. Security

We design the app to process documents locally whenever possible.

You are responsible for controlling access to your device and your files. If you share files from the app, those files may be visible to the apps or services you choose.

## 14. Your Choices

You can control your privacy choices by:

- Granting or denying camera permission
- Granting or denying storage permission
- Revoking permissions from Android settings
- Managing Google ad personalization settings
- Purchasing premium to remove ads
- Clearing app data or uninstalling the app

## 15. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time.

Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated “Last Updated” date.

